cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and its applications to decoding, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of conditional information measures and side information also suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study of list decoding and probability of error could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
